article.description: Mitch McCarron scored 29 points and grabbed nine rebounds as Metro State outlasted Elon for a 75-74 upset Monday night.
article.shortLinkText: Division II Metro State edges Elon for upset
article.headline: Mitch McCarron drives Division II Metro State to upset of Elon
article.linkText: Division II Metro State edges Elon for upset
article.story:
ELON, N.C. -- Mitch McCarron scored 29 points and grabbed nine rebounds as Metro State outlasted Elon for a 75-74 upset Monday night.

Metro State, the No. 1-ranked team in Division II, used a 21-10 run capped by a Raul Delgado 3-pointer to take its largest lead of 16 late in the first half.

Elon (2-4) climbed back as Sebastian Koch hit a 3-pointer, Lucas Troutman made a pair of free throws and Tanner Samson netted another triple to make the score 73-72 with 1:24 remaining.

The teams exchanged free throws to make the score 75-74. After a missed free throw by McCarron, Koch missed the potential go-ahead layup, and Troutman's offensive rebound and putback as time expired didn't fall, either, giving the Phoenix their fourth straight loss.

Austin Hamilton had 15 points and six assists to pace Elon.

Nicholas Kay scored 13 points for the Roadrunners, and Delgado added 11.
